title: -Measurement of The Angle-Integrated Secondary Neutron Spectra From Interaction of 14 Mev Neutrons With Medium and Heavy Nuclei-.

x4codes.hlp: Inst. fuer Isotopenforschung und Kernphysik, Vienna, Austria

x4freetext: PREPRINT OF ARICLE TO APPEARE IN THE
PROCEEDINGS OF THE BNL CONFERENCE 12-14 MAY 1980.

x4codes.shortRef: Conf: Zentralinst. f. Kernforschung Rossendorf Reports, No.382, p.159 (1979)

x4freetext: SPECTRA FROM INTERACTION OF 14 MEV NEUTRONS WITH
A PULSED 250 KEV COCKROFT WALTON ACCELERATOR.
.HOLLOW CYLINDERS OF ABOUT 6 CM3 WITH NATURAL ISOTOPIC
CALIBRATION BETWEEN 0.25 AND 6 MEV NEUTRON ENERGY.
.THE EXPERIMENTAL RESULTS ARE COMPARED WITH EXISTING
MEASUREMENTS AND WITH STATISTICAL MODEL CALCULATIONS
SCATTERED IN SAMPLE TO 14.7 MEV PEAK.
.THE ERRORS GIVEN WERE OBTAINED BY QUADRATIC ADDITI
OF THE STATISTICAL ERRORS ESTIMATED 1 SIGMA ERRORS FO
FOR ALL IDENTIFIED SOURCES OF SYSTEMATIC ERRORS AND
THUS CORRESPOND TO EFFECTIVE 1 SIGMA ERRORS. THE
FOLLOWING CONTRIBUTIONS ARE INCLUDED IN THE ERROR
- THE TOTAL STATISTICAL ERROR INCLUDING THE ERROR
- THE UNCERTAINTY IN THE FORM OF THE CF-252
- THE ERROR IN THE ABSORBTION CORRECTION FACTOR FOR
- THE ERROR FOR THE MULTIPLE SCATTERING CORRECTION,
- AN UNCERTAINTY OF 1.5 PERCENT WAS ASSUMED FOR THE
NORMALIZATION FACTORS USED IN THE BACKGROUND
- A 3 PERCENT EFFICIENCY ERROR FOR THE 14.7 MEV
